						<summary>

						

						<p>Slab from Errakōṭa, now being preserved at Jagdālpūr.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">[Nṛipa*]ti-bhūshaṇa Śaka 945: 1023 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This incomplete epigraph furnishes the details of date viz., Śaka 945, Rudhirōdgāri, Vaiśākha śu 3, Thursday.</p>						

						<p>It refers to [Nṛipa*]ti-bhūshaṇa-mahāraju as belonging to Chinda-kula and Nāgavaṁśa. Other details are lost. Just as Rājabhūshaṇa was a surname of king Sōmēśvara I, <hi rend="italic">[Nṛipa*]ti-bhūshaṇa</hi> was another surname for him.</p>						

						</summary>
